Problem encountered when trying to run ssh commands right after start.

The `SSH` function just throws errors, if the VM and the SSH is not running 😟

```go
        if !v.isRunning() {
                return errors.Errorf("vm %q is not running.", v.Name)
        }
```

So I was trying to add some code, that could wait _until_ it was able to run it...

For now I think it just needs to sleep for a second or two, when running on darwin
